        <body>
            <img src="https://cityoftoronto--c.na78.content.force.com/servlet/servlet.ImageServer?id=0151N000003Zcji&oid=00Do0000000bTwm" width="700" height="160" /> <br/><br/>            
            <p>{!case(month(today()),1,'January',2,'February',3,'March',4,'April',5,'May',6,'June',7,'July',8,'August',9,'September',10,'October',11,'November','December')} {!Day(TODAY())}, {!YEAR(TODAY())}</p>
            <p>Re:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; BIA Innovation Fund<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{!relatedTo.Account__r.BillingStreet}, {!relatedTo.Account__r.BillingCity}, {!relatedTo.Account__r.BillingPostalCode}<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;File No.: {!relatedTo.Financial_Incentive_Name__c}</p>
            <p>Dear {!RelatedTo.Account__r.Name},</p>
            <p>Your application for funding under the City of Toronto&rsquo;s BIA Innovation Fund has been approved in the amount of {!relatedTo.Amount_Approved_Formula__c} for the project described in your original application. This is the maximum amount you will receive under the grant, including any applicable taxes and disbursements. The grant is based on the BIA Innovation Fund Program Guidelines. If the final project expenses are less than the approved amount, the grant will be reduced accordingly. The funding must be used only for the project scope described in your original application. Any major changes to the project scope must be approved in writing by the Manager, Toronto BIA Office.</p>
            <p>The funds will be payable in two installments. The first installment is upon receipt of this signed Letter of Understanding. The second installment is paid after completion and delivery of final project documentation. To obtain either of the installments, the Recipient must submit required documentation listed in the Terms and Conditions.</p>
            <p>The Terms and Conditions of the grant are set out in this letter and Appendix 1 attached hereto which taken together form the agreement. If you breach any of the terms and conditions of this agreement, if you knowingly provided false information in the application, use funds for purposes not approved, or breach any of the provisions of the Ontario Human Rights Code in your operation, the funding must, at the request of the City be repaid in whole or in part.</p>
            <p>Please make an additional copy of this Letter of Understanding for your files. Sign and return the original letter of understanding to the address below:</p>
            <p>David Hessels<br />Economic Partnership Advisor<br />Economic Development &amp; Culture Division<br />City of Toronto<br />77 Elizabeth Street, 2nd Floor<br />Toronto, Ontario M5G 1P4</p>
            <p>Your application will not be processed until a signed copy of this Letter of Understanding is received by this office. If you commence the Work described in your application prior to returning a signed copy of this letter, you will become ineligible for the Commercial Fa&ccedil;ade Improvement Program. Upon satisfactory completion of the fa&ccedil;ade improvements and all program requirements, arrangements will be made for you to receive your cheque.</p>
            <p>Sincerely,</p>
            <p>Mike Major<br />Manager, BIA Office<br />Business Growth Services<br />Economic Development &amp; Culture Division<br />City of Toronto</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p>I/We have read, understand and agree to comply with the terms and conditions in Appendix 1, attached and in this Letter of Understanding.</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p>Name:<br /><br />Title:<br /><br />Signature:<br /><br />Date:</p>
